\f0\fs70 \cf2 Lemon Gelato
\f1\fs50 \cf3 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl280\ql\qnatural

\fs40 \cf3 Yield: 1-1/2 quarts (
\fs38 \cf3 8 Servings)
\fs50 \cf3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\ql\qnatural
\cf3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\ql\qnatural

\f0\fs58 \cf2 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl280\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\fs50 \cf3 		1 cup milk\
		1 cup sugar\
		5 egg yolks, lightly beaten\
		3 tablespoons grated lemon peel\
		3/4 cup lemon juice\
		2 cups heavy whipping cream\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\ql\qnatural

\f0\fs58 \cf2 Directions\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl280\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\fs50 \cf3 		In a small heavy saucepan, heat milk to 175\'b0; stir in sugar until\
		dissolved. Whisk a small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks.\
		Return all to the pan, whisking constantly. Add lemon peel. Cook and stir over low heat until mixture reaches at least 160\'b0 and coats the back of a metal spoon.
\fs58 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\fs50 		Remove from the heat; strain. Stir in lemon juice. Cool quickly by placing pan in a bowl of ice water; stir for 2 minutes. Stir in\
		cream. Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
\fs58 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\fs50 		Fill cylinder of ice cream freezer two-thirds full; freeze according to manufacturer's directions. Transfer to a freezer container; freeze for 2-4 hours before serving. 
